observations.recommendation:
Management to:
a. Evaluate the viability of projects/programs/activities that were not implemented during the year to determine its cause/s of their non-implementation and to fast-track thereafter the implementation of the same;
b. For projects/programs which are no longer considered as priority, it may opt to reprogram said appropriations to finance other priority development projects;
c. Reprogram the balances of appropriations of completed projects to finance other priority development projects; and
d. Closely monitor the offices responsible for its implementation to pursue the timely and full implementation of all projects/programs, as planned.

Management to:
1. Require the Bids and Awards Committee to furnish the accounting unit of the certified true copies of Charge Sales Invoice/DR/OR of those items which remained unpaid at the end of the year;
2. Direct the Municipal Accountant to determine those invalid obligations and effect the necessary adjustments;
3. Recognize Accounts payable in the books of accounts only when goods and services are accepted/rendered or creditor/contractor’s billing statements are received. The required supporting documents are to be attached to its corresponding JEVs; and
4. Disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements those items which were not yet delivered but already obligated and reported in the Statement of Appropriations, Allotments, Obligations and Balances.

